The idea that all AI models respond the same way to prompts is a myth. It's just not true.

People act like a prompt is a prompt—that any AI will understand it the same way. But these models are built differently. They each have their own training data and internal logic. A prompt that works perfectly for GPT-4 might confuse Claude. Something written for Bard could totally miss with Llama.

These models don’t “read between the lines.” They read exactly what you write. (1/2)
